00:16:30:130000.Scene: Leonard and Sheldon, Inside Leonard’s car
00:16:30:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:30:130000.Dialogue: Why can't she get her own TV?

00:16:32:110000.Scene: Leonard and Sheldon, Inside Leonard’s car
00:16:32:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:32:110000.Dialogue: Come on, you know how it is with breakups.

00:16:34:100000.Scene: Leonard and Sheldon, Inside Leonard’s car
00:16:34:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:34:100000.Dialogue: No, I don't... and neither do you.

00:16:37:180000.Scene: Leonard and Sheldon, Inside Leonard’s car
00:16:37:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:37:180000.Dialogue: I broke up with Joyce Kim.

00:16:39:080000.Scene: Leonard and Sheldon, Inside Leonard’s car
00:16:39:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:39:080000.Dialogue: You did not break up with Joyce Kim. She defected to North Korea.

00:16:42:210000.Scene: Leonard and Sheldon, Inside Leonard’s car
00:16:42:210000.Speaker: Leonard

00:16:48:010000.Scene: Leonard and Sheldon, Inside Leonard’s car
00:16:48:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:48:010000.Dialogue: This situation is much less complicated. There's some kind of dispute between Penny and her ex-boyfriend as to who gets custody of the TV. She just wanted to avoid having a scene with him.

00:16:57:130000.Scene: Leonard and Sheldon, Inside Leonard’s car
00:16:57:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:57:130000.Dialogue: No, there's not going to be a scene. There's two of us and one of him.

00:17:03:210000.Scene: Leonard and Sheldon, Inside Leonard’s car
00:17:03:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:03:210000.Dialogue: Leonard, the two of us can't even carry a TV.

00:17:08:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:08:150000.Dialogue: So, you guys work with Leonard and Sheldon at the university?

00:17:17:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:17:070000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, do you speak English?

00:17:20:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:20:040000.Dialogue: He speaks English. He just can't speak to women.

00:17:49:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:49:050000.Dialogue: We're not going to give up just like that.

00:17:51:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:51:060000.Dialogue: Leonard, the TV's in the building. We've been denied access to the building, ergo, we are done.

00:17:55:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:55:190000.Dialogue: Excuse me. If I were to give up on the first little hitch, I never would have identified the fingerprints of string theory in the aftermath of the Big Bang.

00:18:20:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:20:230000.Dialogue: It's just a privilege to watch your mind at work.

00:18:24:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:24:170000.Dialogue: Come on, we have a combined IQ of 360. We should be able to figure out how to get into a stupid building.

00:18:34:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:34:130000.Dialogue: What do you think their combined IQ is?

00:18:39:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:39:230000.Dialogue: This is it. I'll do the talking.

00:18:43:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:43:230000.Dialogue: Good thinking. I'll just be the muscle.

00:19:00:040000.Speaker: Man
00:19:00:040000.Dialogue: How the hell did you get in the building?

00:19:21:090000.Scene: Outside the apartment building. Leonard and Sheldon exit. They are not wearing trousers.
00:19:21:090000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:19:23:040000.Scene: Outside the apartment building. Leonard and Sheldon exit. They are not wearing trousers.
00:19:23:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:23:040000.Dialogue: My mom bought me those pants.

00:19:27:010000.Scene: Outside the apartment building. Leonard and Sheldon exit. They are not wearing trousers.
00:19:27:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:27:010000.Dialogue: You're going to have to call her.

00:19:31:150000.Scene: On the stairs of Sheldon and Leonard’s building.
00:19:31:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:31:150000.Dialogue: Sheldon, I am so sorry I dragged you through this.

00:19:34:160000.Scene: On the stairs of Sheldon and Leonard’s building.
00:19:34:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:34:160000.Dialogue: It's okay. It wasn't my first pantsing and it won't be my last.

00:19:39:060000.Scene: On the stairs of Sheldon and Leonard’s building.
00:19:39:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:39:060000.Dialogue: And you were right about my motives. I was hoping to establish a relationship with Penny that might have someday led to sex.

00:19:47:150000.Scene: On the stairs of Sheldon and Leonard’s building.
00:19:47:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:47:150000.Dialogue: Well, you got me out of my pants.

00:19:51:140000.Scene: On the stairs of Sheldon and Leonard’s building.
00:19:51:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:51:140000.Dialogue: Anyway, I've learned my lesson. She's out of my league, I'm done with her. Got my work, one day I'll win the Nobel Prize and then I'll die alone.

00:19:59:190000.Scene: On the stairs of Sheldon and Leonard’s building.
00:19:59:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:59:190000.Dialogue: Don't think like that. You're not going to die alone.

00:20:02:210000.Scene: On the stairs of Sheldon and Leonard’s building.
00:20:02:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:02:210000.Dialogue: Thank you, Sheldon. You're a good friend.

00:20:07:000000.Scene: On the stairs of Sheldon and Leonard’s building.
00:20:07:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:07:000000.Dialogue: And you're certainly not going to win a Nobel Prize.

00:20:10:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:20:10:130000.Dialogue: This is one of my favorite places to kick back after a quest. They have a great house ale.

00:20:17:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:20:17:170000.Dialogue: Yeah, I've had him since level ten.

00:20:23:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:20:23:040000.Dialogue: Anyway, if you had your own game character we could hang out, maybe go on a quest.

00:20:32:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:20:32:080000.Dialogue: I don't think I'll be able to stop thinking about it.

00:20:43:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:43:140000.Dialogue: Well, your ex-boyfriend sends his regards and I think the rest is fairly self-explanatory.

00:20:49:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:20:49:060000.Dialogue: I'm so sorry. I really thought if you guys went instead of me he wouldn't be such an ass.

00:20:54:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:54:000000.Dialogue: What is happening to you? That was a valid...?

00:20:59:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:20:59:220000.Dialogue: Really, thank you so much for going and trying, you're just... You're so terrific. Really.

00:21:08:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:21:08:090000.Dialogue: Why don't you put some clothes on, I'll get my purse, and dinner is on me, okay?

00:21:23:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:21:23:070000.Dialogue: Are babies will be smart and beautiful.

00:21:35:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:21:35:180000.Dialogue: Is Thai food okay with you, Penny?

00:21:37:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:21:37:180000.Dialogue: We can't have Thai food, we had Indian for lunch.

00:21:43:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:21:43:090000.Dialogue: It would be gastronomically redundant. I can see we're going to have to spell out everything for this girl.

00:21:53:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:21:53:110000.Dialogue: Turn left on Lake Street and head up to Colorado. I know a wonderful little sushi bar that has karaoke.

00:22:13:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:22:13:060000.Dialogue: I don't know what your odds are in the world as a whole, but as far as the population of this car goes, you're a veritable mack daddy.
